  <bioghist id="55f9cd7040f237e0f2454f283394b39a">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Linda Atkinson worked as a program officer at the Ford Foundation for a number of years. She started in the Foundation's Population Program before moving to the Urban Poverty Program following an organizational change in the Foundation's programming.</p><p>Atkinson's post-Ford Foundation career included her position as director of clinical development at the AZLA Corporation, a pharmaceutical and medical systems company. She has been involved with the South San Mateo County League of Women Voters since 2018.</p><p>Prior to joining the Ford Foundation, Atkinson had a research position at the Population Council. She earned a B.S. in biology from Wheaton College and a Ph.D. in human physiology from the University of Illinois' College of Medicine.</p>  </bioghist>
